%T A397752 17515,33231,63301,120336,229242,436243,831081,1582393,3014656,
%U A397752 5741602,10938581,20836350,39696471,75621773,144071590,274467744,522905796,996198474,1897921983,3615811108
%N A397752 Number of unlabeled bridgeless polygonal snake graphs with n vertices.
%C A397752 A bridgeless polygonal snake graph consists of a chain of cycle graphs. Each cut vertex connects two cycles and each cycle has at most two cut vertices. Graphs are counted up to graph isomorphism.
%C A397752 Snakes are a subclass of cactus graphs. The triangular snake graph is the polygonal snake in which each cycle is a triangle.
%H A397752 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A397752/b397752.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A397752 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/TriangularSnakeGraph.html">Triangular Snake Graph</a>.
%H A397752 <a href="/index/Rec#order_12">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1,3,-1,-1,-2,-3,0,1,1,2,0,-1).
%F A397752 G.f.: x^3*(1 - 2*x^2 - 2*x^3 - 2*x^4 + x^5 + 2*x^6 + 2*x^7 + 2*x^8 - x^10)/((1 - x - 2*x^2 + x^4)*(1 + x - x^4)*(1 - x - x^4)).
%e A397752 a(7) = A035085(7) - 1 = 4 counts all polygonal cacti on 7 vertices except three triangles joined at a single cut vertex.
%e A397752 a(8) = 6 counts: an octagon, a hexagon joined to a triangle, a pentagon joined to square, and the 3 configurations of a square and two triangles shown below.
%e A397752    o---o  o    o       o  o---o  o       o  o---o----o
%e A397752    |   | / \  / \     / \ |   | / \     / \ |   | \ /
%e A397752    o---o----o----o   o----o---o----o   o----o---o  o
%o A397752 (PARI)
%o A397752 G()={my(ge = x^2/(1 - x), gs=x*(1 + x)/(1 - x^2)^2 - x); x*((ge^2/(1 - gs) + subst(ge/(1 - gs), x, x^2)*(1 + gs))/2 + ge) }
%o A397752 seq(n) = { Vec(G() + O(x*x^n), -n) }
%Y A397752 Cf. A035085 (bridgeless polygonal cacti)
%K A397752 nonn,easy,new
%O A397752 1,5
%A A397752 _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 17 2026
